  "moveStrategies": {
    "cursed-strikes": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "The user strikes a pose with a 30f Startup. Then, fires a projectile that travels >32 studs in 55f before despawning."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "After that, you are left in stun for 25 frames on whiff. If the projectile hits, the user will grab the target and perform a barrage of attacks on them, dealing damage. If the projectile is blocked, the user will get a Block Endlag of 46f, more than punishable for anyone with half a braincell, so do not use this in neutral."
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "[b]The Projectile Thingy:[/b] Because the hit detection is tied to a spawned projectile rather than the user's physical body, the move can grab opponents through solid walls, even if the user doesn't move.",
          "[b]Combo Extender:[/b] While the attacker leaves their grab animation after 113f, the target is forced to endure a total stun of 161 frames. This +48f frame advantage creates a window to link into any attacks in the kit."
        ],
        "author": "Deptr"
      }
    ],
